SIMPLE: zip
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Zip
<hw>Zip</hw> <pr>(z⟦icr⟧p)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Imitative.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>A hissing or sibilant sound such as that made by a
flying bullet.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>a quantity of no importance.</def>
<mark>[informal]</mark>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> nothing, nihil, nichts, nix, nada, aught, cipher,
cypher, goose egg, naught, nil, zero, zilch.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>a device for locking together two toothed edges by
means of a sliding tab.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> slide fastener, zipper, zip-fastener.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Zip</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Zip
<hw>Zip</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To make, or move with, a sound like
a zip{1}.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Zip-fastener</ent>⟦br⟧
